{
  "text": "While the actual SIL hovers above a rotating disk surface, the disk in this work was modeled as a translating surface with a velocity of [CITATION_1] where is the rotational speed of the disk, which was taken as rpm [CITATION_2] , and is the radial distance between the disk and lens centers ( mm). The downstream surface of the domain was specified with a zero-gradient outflow boundary condition, while the upstream surface of the domain was specified with a fully developed Couette velocity profile, as follows: [CITATION_3] where is the overall height of the flow domain, which is m. Additionally, the bounding surfaces at the maximum and minimum -locations of the domain were modeled as slip walls with a specified normal velocity gradient of zero in order to simulate free air flow along the lateral boundaries. The remaining surfaces, including the lens, lens holder, and disk surfaces, were specified to be no-slip walls.",
